snippet.textDisplay:
To all the people giving hateful comments specially the one who are blatantly cursing these artists should understand that  we can criticise constructively and we have full right But i think that we should think it as step towards training our new musicians, singers and producers. Giving them an opportunity to show their talent on a good platform. which has a good viewership in pakistan and abroad. They have taken a right step and what now they are doing is the part of the evolution of this show. You can't have rohail hayat for 30 years. So they now have to focus on the younger generation and give them exposure with our masters from previous generations. So that the masters can transfer their knowledge and inspire the young breed of musicians to make something new that has its roots strong in our culture but is new, refreshing and appealing to the younger generation. Our music industry was on verge of extinction and Rohail and coke studio has made some music that has not only inspired many new musicians but have given platform to a lot of new music stars that were not that well known before. It is only one of the few good things happening to our music industry so we should support all the singers, musicians, producers and directors that are taking part in it. Our constructive criticism should be welcomed and i know that most of the commenting because they have a emotional attachment to this music but lets give this team a little more time to mature. I know they will surprise you. Only thing that i think the coke studio management should have done was to give Rohail Hayat the similar role they have given now to strings(Producers) with strings noori and some others talent as music directors because thats how they have learned under Rohail Hayat. The production quality of sound has lacked under strings and Rohail Hayat got extremely good after experience of producing 5 seasons of coke studio and i think season 6 for me was the best in terms of production quality. That experience should have been transferred to the new producers. 

And for the people who are asking for Rohail to comeback in coke studio.  I would myself request him to come back and maybe do another similar show. This is the right step for our industry and don't expect state of music and musician to be changed if we won't start giving respect and support to the people who after all the odds are still trying to do something in pakistan music industry.
